Ndubuisi Orji, Abuja The House of Representatives has  directed the Inspector General of Police, Ibrahim Idris, to prosecute the Special Adviser and Chairman of the Special Presidential Investigation Panel (SPIP), Chief Okoi Obono-Obla, for forgery and misrepresentation. This is sequel to the adoption of the report of the House Ad-hoc Committee that investigated the legality and modus operandi of the SPIP, at Thursday’s plenary. READ ALSO: APC planning to rig 2019 general elections- Ex Niger governor, Aliyu alleges 